# Auto-strip Jupyter notebook outputs on commit so large cell outputs
# (images, dataframes, log dumps) never enter the repository.  Developers
# see full outputs locally; only the code cells are persisted.
#
# Requires nbstripout: pip install nbstripout
*.ipynb filter=nbstripout
*.ipynb diff=ipynb

# Pin LF for the generated apps-catalog fixture + its generator so the
# fixture-freshness check (gen-apps-catalog-fixture.mjs --check) is byte-stable
# across platforms — the generator always writes LF, so the committed file must
# stay LF or the --check drift gate would falsely fail on a CRLF checkout.
scripts/csa-loom/fixtures/apps-catalog.json text eol=lf
scripts/csa-loom/gen-apps-catalog-fixture.mjs text eol=lf
